benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Add custom fields to bundle

covered: Valid Payload scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04)
gaps: Server error handling with 500 Internal Server Error (only 503 covered in TC15/TC20).
Caching Behavior with ETag/Cache-Control headers not tested.
Rate Limiting / Throttling scenarios not tested (beyond retry concept in TC16).
Pagination is not applicable to POST in this context, but no explicit documentation on handling large result sets (not required for POST).
Authorization boundaries beyond 401 (e.g., 403) not explicitly covered.
Regression tests around edge case semantics (TC21) are present, but broader coverage of case-sensitivity rules across field names could be expanded.
recommendations: Add a test for 500 Internal Server Error to ensure proper server-side failure handling.
Add tests verifying caching headers in responses for POST (if applicable), e.g., ETag/Cache-Control, to align with caching guidelines.
Introduce explicit rate-limiting/throttling tests (beyond client retry behavior) to validate system behavior under load.
Add a 403 Forbidden test scenario to cover authorization boundaries beyond missing/invalid token (e.g., authenticated user without sufficient permissions).
Clarify and extend case-sensitivity behavior for field names with dedicated scenarios to ensure consistent behavior across updates.
